 {"id":"asupersync-28c51.302.38","title":"[net][peer-review] Tighten cancel-aware stream + split-half coverage for TCP and Unix I/O","description":"Bounded peer-review slice under asupersync-28c51.302 on src/net/tcp/stream.rs, src/net/unix/stream.rs, src/net/tcp/split.rs, and src/net/unix/split.rs. Audit the current cancel-awareness diff on nonblocking stream poll paths, patch remaining cancellation gaps on unsplit streams and their split()/into_split() siblings, add focused deterministic regression tests, and validate with rch-backed cargo lanes. Do not widen into src/runtime/state.rs or the active RaptorQ surfaces.","notes":"2026-04-11 MaroonPlateau: audited the current TCP/runtime cancel-check diff and found a real semantic regression. The new low-level cancel checks were correct, but src/net/tcp/stream.rs still treated Interrupted-under-cancel as a per-address failure in the multi-address connect loops, and src/net/websocket/client.rs downgraded cancelled TCP connect to WsConnectError::Io. Patched both boundaries and added focused regression coverage in src/net/tcp/stream.rs plus mapping tests in src/net/websocket/client.rs. Validation via rch: cargo check -p asupersync --lib PASS; cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings PASS; cargo test -p asupersync --lib connect_resolved_addrs_ -- --nocapture PASS (2 tests). Repo-wide gates are currently blocked by unrelated dirty-tree issues: cargo fmt --check fails on multiple pre-existing files; cargo check --all-targets and cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings both fail in src/net/unix/stream.rs test code on a stale/unrelated futures_task::noop_waker compile frontier. Agent Mail remains degraded read-only, so bead notes are the durable coordination record for this slice.\n\n2026-04-11 FrostyHawk: followed the remaining cancel-safety hole through the sibling APIs and closed it. Added pre-effect cancellation guards on `poll_flush`/`poll_shutdown` for unsplit TCP and Unix streams, plus matching read/write/flush/shutdown guards for borrowed and owned TCP/Unix split halves. Added six focused regression tests covering cancelled unsplit flush/shutdown and cancelled borrowed/owned split read+write paths. Validation via rch: `cargo test -p asupersync --lib return_interrupted_when_cancel_requested -- --nocapture` PASS (6 tests); `cargo check --all-targets` PASS; `cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings` PASS. `cargo fmt --check` still reports unrelated pre-existing formatting drift in many files outside this slice.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FrostyHawk","created_at":"2026-04-11T23:10:49.762758475Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-11T23:46:30Z","closed_at":"2026-04-11T23:46:30Z","close_reason":"Completed: closed the remaining TCP/Unix stream and split-half cancellation gap, added focused regressions, and validated with rch-backed test/check/clippy gates.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cancel","net","peer-review","tcp","unix"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302.38","depends_on_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-11T23:10:49.762758475Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-28c51.302.39","title":"[peer-review][net] Audit datagram cancel-awareness diff for UDP and UnixDatagram","description":"Bounded peer-review slice for the live cancel-awareness diff in src/net/udp.rs and src/net/unix/datagram.rs. Verify the newly added Cx::current cancellation gates preserve datagram semantics, reactor registration behavior, and no-ambient-authority expectations; patch any real bug found, add focused regression coverage, and validate only with rch-offloaded cargo lanes on the touched surface.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"AzurePanther","created_at":"2026-04-12T01:23:45.248910652Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-12T01:43:43.311759548Z","closed_at":"2026-04-12T01:43:43.311425467Z","close_reason":"Added missing UnixDatagram cancellation gates for peek/ready paths and regression tests; rch lib tests pass, cargo check passes, unrelated fmt/clippy failures remain elsewhere.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cancel","net","peer-review"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302.39","depends_on_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-12T01:23:45.248910652Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-28c51.302.4","title":"[RANDOM-AUDIT][service/sync] Audit and fix buffer+semaphore changed-surface regressions","description":"Review changed surfaces in src/service/buffer.rs and src/sync/semaphore.rs for correctness/regression issues, apply fixes, and validate with rch-offloaded targeted checks.","notes":"Implemented fix in src/service/buffer.rs: poll_ready now uses consistent lock order (pending -> ready_wakers) to match completion/drop paths and deduplicates repeated waker registration when full. Added unit test poll_ready_deduplicates_waker_when_full. Validation: rch exec -- cargo check --lib (pass), rch exec -- cargo check --all-targets (pass), rch exec -- cargo test --lib service::buffer::tests::poll_ready_deduplicates_waker_when_full -- --exact --nocapture (pass). Workspace-wide clippy still failing in unrelated files: src/combinator/rate_limit.rs, src/runtime/blocking_pool.rs, src/runtime/timer.rs, src/raptorq/gf256.rs.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CopperCastle","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-03-05T02:41:17.472741159Z","created_by":"CopperCastle","updated_at":"2026-03-05T02:58:34.612100851Z","closed_at":"2026-03-05T02:58:34.612075814Z","close_reason":"Completed: fixed buffer lock-order inversion and waker dedup regression; added regression test and validated via rch.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["buffer","random-audit","semaphore","service","sync"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302.4","depends_on_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-05T02:41:17.472741159Z","created_by":"CopperCastle","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
