 {"id":"asupersync-28c51.302.5","title":"[RANDOM-AUDIT][scheduler] Skip benign singleton spectral history while preserving trapped self-cycles","description":"Peer-review follow-up under asupersync-28c51.302. The recent trapped-cycle fix in src/runtime/scheduler/three_lane.rs broadened the live spectral-monitor guard from wait_graph_nodes > 1 to > 0. Because wait_graph_signals_from_state counts every non-terminal task, that change started recording spectral history for ordinary singleton live-task states with zero wait edges, altering the governor/decision-contract live path for degenerate graphs that carry no dependency structure. Scope: narrow the guard so singleton graphs are analyzed only when they actually carry a trapped self-cycle, add focused regression coverage for the benign-singleton and trapped-self-cycle cases, and validate with rch-backed cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"AmberSnow","created_at":"2026-03-21T02:12:06.525561935Z","created_by":"AmberSnow","updated_at":"2026-03-21T02:12:59.931852125Z","closed_at":"2026-03-21T02:12:59.931826287Z","close_reason":"Fixed singleton spectral-history regression in three_lane governor path","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302.5","depends_on_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T02:12:06.525561935Z","created_by":"AmberSnow","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-28c51.302.6","title":"[RANDOM-AUDIT][process] Avoid blocking runtime-thread drop while preserving kill_on_drop reaping","description":"Fresh peer-review slice over the live src/process.rs changed surface. Current diff fixes zombie reaping by replacing Child::drop kill_on_drop cleanup from nonblocking try_wait() to blocking wait(). Scope: preserve the new no-zombie guarantee while avoiding surprise blocking on runtime worker threads when kill_on_drop children are dropped under an ambient Cx. Add focused deterministic regression coverage for branch selection / cleanup semantics and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BrightCreek","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-03-21T02:33:10.454426100Z","created_by":"BrightCreek","updated_at":"2026-03-21T02:52:04.156894399Z","closed_at":"2026-03-21T02:52:00.625568462Z","close_reason":"Implemented and validated bounded process follow-up; remaining failures are unrelated repo-wide or infra issues","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302.6","depends_on_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T02:33:10.454426100Z","created_by":"BrightCreek","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2568,"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302.6","author":"BrightCreek","text":"Implemented bounded follow-up in src/process.rs: keep the no-zombie kill_on_drop reap guarantee, but avoid blocking Drop on runtime threads by backgrounding the wait() path when an ambient Cx is installed; keep direct synchronous reap when no ambient Cx exists. Added a focused ambient-Cx branch-selection regression alongside the Unix reap regression already on this surface. Validation: rustfmt +nightly --edition 2024 --check src/process.rs ✅; git diff --check -- src/process.rs ✅; rch exec -- cargo check -p asupersync --lib ✅; rch exec -- cargo test -p asupersync --lib kill_on_drop -- --nocapture ✅ on the pre-lint-fix version of the same code path (3 relevant tests passed). Follow-up focused offloaded clippy on -p asupersync --lib initially flagged two src/process.rs temporaries with significant Drop in the new helper; fixed by binding the mutex guards explicitly. Rerun via rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/var/tmp CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/var/tmp/rch-brightcreek-process-clippy2 cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib --message-format short -- -D warnings no longer reports src/process.rs; remaining failures are pre-existing in src/lab/dual_run.rs, src/net/tcp/stream.rs, src/record/symbolic_obligation.rs, src/spork.rs, and src/transport/router.rs. Broader rch exec -- cargo check --all-targets / cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings were infrastructure-blocked by remote timeout -> local fallback hitting stale-nightly artifacts and/or worker space pressure, not by this slice. A post-fix exact test rerun is still sitting in the repo’s known silent-wrapper phase after compile, but the only code change after the earlier green selector was the clippy-driven guard-binding rewrite with no behavioral change.","created_at":"2026-03-21T02:51:28Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-28c51.302.7","title":"[peer-review][channel] Clear current lib clippy blockers in mpsc/session helpers","description":"Current live tree still has channel helper diffs in src/channel/mpsc.rs and src/channel/session.rs, and multiple agents report lib clippy failures remaining on those two files after the scope/state/task_inspector follow-ups were fixed. Take a bounded peer-review slice over the convenience send/reserve helpers, clear the current clippy blockers without changing channel semantics, add/update focused validation evidence via rch, and coordinate explicitly with the adjacent deadlock_test compile-frontier owners.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CobaltGlen","created_at":"2026-03-30T02:27:08.346033646Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-30T02:36:41.822332849Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T02:36:41.821873215Z","close_reason":"Completed: channel helper lib clippy/check/fmt frontier cleared; session helper simplification landed and audit recorded","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["channel","clippy","peer-review"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-28c51.302.7","depends_on_id":"asupersync-28c51.302","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T02:27:08.346033646Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
