 {"id":"asupersync-3bsp5.10","title":"[RAPTORQ-RFC6330][E3][H2-support] Refresh active upstream Track-E blocker from 36m6p.23 to 36m6p","description":"Bounded H2 support slice: refresh the closure-packet/doc/test trio so the active upstream Track-E blocker reflects the live Beads graph after asupersync-36m6p.23 closed. Scope is limited to artifacts/raptorq_program_closure_signoff_packet_v1.json, docs/raptorq_program_closure_signoff_packet.md, and tests/raptorq_perf_invariants.rs. Do not touch active E5 implementation surfaces.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Codex","created_at":"2026-04-11T00:15:02.862876829Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-11T00:22:45.567288129Z","closed_at":"2026-04-11T00:22:45.566863759Z","close_reason":"Completed: H2 active Track-E blocker truthfulness refreshed and validated","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-3bsp5.10","depends_on_id":"asupersync-3bsp5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-11T00:15:02.862876829Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":3151,"issue_id":"asupersync-3bsp5.10","author":"Codex","text":"[2026-04-10 Codex] Completed the bounded H2 truthfulness refresh on artifacts/raptorq_program_closure_signoff_packet_v1.json, docs/raptorq_program_closure_signoff_packet.md, and tests/raptorq_perf_invariants.rs.\n\nProblem found:\n- The H2 packet/doc/invariants still treated `asupersync-36m6p.23` as the active upstream Track-E leaf even though `br show asupersync-36m6p.23 --json` now reports it closed.\n- The live blocker is `asupersync-36m6p` itself (still `in_progress` with no open child leaves), so the blocked-state contract was stale.\n\nWhat changed:\n- Track-E `status_reason` now names `asupersync-36m6p` as the active E5 blocker instead of the closed child bead.\n- H2 replay `status_snapshot_contract.required_bead_ids` now tracks `asupersync-36m6p`.\n- Residual risk `RQ-H2-R2` now ma